<H1>    ISDSTIME() </H1>


<H2> Fortran version: </H2>
<PRE>
    INTEGER FUNCTION  ISDSTIME( JDATE )
        INTEGER, INTENT(IN   ) :: JDATE	!  Julian date (YYYYDDD)
</PRE><P>

<H2> No C version:   </H2>

<H2> Summary: </H2>

    <VAR>ISDSTIME()</VAR> returns <CODE>TRUE</CODE> if and only if
    daylight savings time is in effect for the
    <A HREF = "DATETIME.html"> Julian date <CODE>JDATE</CODE></A>,
    using the Zeller's-congruence algorithm to find the start and end
    for DST.  Handles both pre-2007 (starts first Sunday in April, ends
    last Sunday in October) and 2007-and-after (second Sunday in March,
    first Sunday in November).
    <P>

    For Fortran-90 declarations and interface checking:
    <PRE>
    <A HREF = "M3UTILIO.html">USE M3UTILIO</A>
    </PRE><P>

    <STRONG>See also</STRONG> subroutines
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <A HREF = "DAYMON.html"> DAYMON()</A>,<BR>
    <A HREF = "HHMMSS.html"> HHMMSS()</A>,<BR>
    <A HREF = "JULIAN.html"> JULIAN()</A>,<BR>
    <A HREF = "MMDDYY.html"> MMDDYY()</A>,<BR>
    <A HREF = "WKDAY.html">  WKDAY()</A>,<BR>
    and <A HREF = "DT2STR.html"> DT2STR() </A><BR>
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
    as well as EDSS/ Models-3 date-time manipulation programs
    <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <A HREF = "GREGDATE.html"> <STRONG>gregdate</STRONG></A> and<BR>
    <A HREF = "JULDATE.html">  <STRONG> juldate</STRONG></A>.
    </BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P>


<H2> Preconditions:   </H2>

    JDATE represented according to EDSS/Models-3
    <A HREF = "DATETIME.html"> date and time conventions </A>
<P>

<H2> Fortran Usage: </H2>

<PRE>
    ...
    USE M3UTILIO
    ...
    LOGICAL   ISDSTIME
    INTEGER   JDATE
    ...
    IF ( ISDSTIME( JDATE ) ) THEN
        !!  ...daylight savings time in effect
        ...
    ELSE
        !!  ...daylight savings time NOT in effect
        ...
    END IF
    ...
</PRE><P>



